<subSubSection pageId="4" pageNumber="261" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1437,1482,2013]" pageId="4" pageNumber="261">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,322,1554,1580]" pageId="4" pageNumber="261">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
The new species is similar to 
<taxonomicName authority="Wang &amp; Zhu, 2020" authorityName="Wang &amp; Zhu" authorityYear="2020" box="[677,845,1555,1581]" class="Insecta" family="Cosmopterigidae" genus="Meleonoma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="261" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="microdonta" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[677,845,1555,1581]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="261">M. microdonta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[854,946,1555,1581]" pageId="4" pageNumber="261">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[854,946,1555,1581]" pageId="4" pageNumber="261" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
in the forewing pattern, but can be distinguished by the valva with a large, sub-triangular process at base on the ventral margin that is longer than the median width of the valva, the saccus ovately dilated distally and the aedeagus without a cornutus in the male genitalia; in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Wang &amp; Zhu" authorityYear="2020" box="[151,317,1663,1689]" class="Insecta" family="Cosmopterigidae" genus="Meleonoma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="261" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="microdonta">
<emphasis box="[151,317,1663,1689]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="261">M. microdonta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, the valva has a small triangular process at base on the ventral margin that is distinctly shorter than the median width of the valva, the saccus is not dilated distally, and the aedeagus has a spine-shaped cornutus.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="5" lastPageNumber="262" pageId="4" pageNumber="261" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1437,1482,2013]" box="[199,805,1734,1761]" pageId="4" pageNumber="261">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,345,1734,1760]" pageId="4" pageNumber="261">Description.</emphasis>
Adult (
<figureCitation box="[431,500,1735,1761]" captionStart="FIGURES 3–8" captionStartId="8.[151,264,1950,1974]" captionTargetBox="[177,1408,883,1925]" captionTargetId="figure-260@8.[171,1416,879,1931]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURES 3–8. Adults of Meleonoma spp. 3, M. acutata sp. nov., ♂; 4, M. basiprocessa sp. nov., ♂; 5, M. bicornea sp. nov., ♂; 6, M. bidigitata sp. nov., ♂; 7, M. circinans sp. nov., ♂; 8, M. compacta sp. nov., ♂. All holotypes. Scales = 2.0 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4283664" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4283664/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="261">Fig. 4</figureCitation>
). Forewing length 5.0 mm.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1437,1482,2013]" pageId="4" pageNumber="261">
<emphasis box="[199,260,1771,1797]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="261">Head</emphasis>
greyish brown, yellow laterally; occiput yellow, tipped blackish brown medially. Labial palpus with first and second segments blackish brown, mixed with yellow scales; second segment with an indistinct yellow ring before apex; third segment yellow, with scattered blackish-brown scales. Antenna with scape blackish brown except yellow at apex; flagellum yellow, alternated with blackish brown on dorsal surface.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1437,1482,2013]" lastBlockId="5.[151,1437,151,1005]" lastPageId="5" lastPageNumber="262" pageId="4" pageNumber="261">
<emphasis box="[199,280,1915,1941]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="261">Thorax</emphasis>
and tegula blackish brown mixed with yellow scales. Forewing narrowly elongate, pointed at apex; ground colour yellow, with dense black scales; costal margin with a rounded black spot at base, with a large black stripe extending from beyond basal spot widened to about basal 1/3; costal spot black, triangular, from basal 2/5 widened to before distal 1/3 horizontally; apical patch black, wide, sub-rectangular, running from apex along termen to tornus; tornal spot fused with apical patch; fold with an ovate black spot at distal 2/7; cell with an ovate black spot at basal 3/5, with smaller rounded black spot at anterior and posterior angles, touching costal spot and tornal spot respectively; dorsum with a wide black stripe on basal 2/3; fringe yellow, blackish brown before apex and around tornus. Hindwing and fringe brown. Legs yellow; on ventral surface, fore coxa blackish brown except yellow apically, femora of fore- and midlegs blackish brown except yellow apically, hind femur blackish brown, tarsi of fore- and midlegs blackish brown except yellow at base of basal tarsomere and at apices of basal two and apical one tarsomeres, hind tarsus with basal four tarsomeres blackish brown except yellow at apices, all tibiae blackish brown except yellow apically.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,151,1005]" pageId="5" pageNumber="262">
<emphasis box="[199,363,475,501]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="262">Male genitalia</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[377,460,475,502]" captionStart="FIGURES 25–30" captionStartId="26.[151,264,1881,1905]" captionTargetBox="[215,1380,187,1861]" captionTargetId="figure-29@26.[193,1393,176,1862]" captionTargetPageId="26" captionText="FIGURES 25–30. Male genitalia of Meleonoma spp. 25, M. acutata sp. nov., paratype, slide No. YAH15102; 26, M. basiprocessa sp. nov., holotype, slide No. YAH15170; 27, M. bicornea sp. nov., holotype, slide No. YAH15106; 28, M. bidigitata sp. nov., paratype, slide No. YAH15459; 29, M. circinans sp. nov., holotype, slide No. YAH15397; 30, M. compacta sp. nov., holotype, slide No. YAH15073. Scales = 0.2 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4283672" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4283672/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="262">Fig. 26</figureCitation>
). Uncus with basal 3/4 broad, distal 1/4 tapered to apex, with dense short setae. Gnathos heavily sclerotized laterally, fused with tegumen anteriorly, not reaching anterior margin of tegumen. Tegumen inverted U-shaped; lateral arm elongate, uniformly wide except narrower at apex. Valva wide at base, slightly narrowed to basal 2/5, widened from basal 2/5 to middle, thereafter narrowed to rounded apex, with dense long setae; ventral margin with a large sub-triangular process at base, longer than median width of valva, rounded at apex; costa narrow, convex near base, reaching before apex; transtilla short, sub-cylindrical, slightly narrowed to rounded apex, medially joined by a membranous band. Sacculus sub-quadrate, with a curved vertical ridge before apex; apex shallowly concave, forming a triangular dorsal process and a smaller sub-rounded ventral process bearing a few tiny denticles. Saccus large and elongate, longer than uncus, ovately dilated distally, with a vertical fold along midline reaching before apex. Juxta arched in semicircle. Aedeagus with basal 3/4 tubular; distal 1/4 inflated, with two curved ribbon-like sclerites.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,151,1005]" box="[199,401,871,897]" pageId="5" pageNumber="262">Female unknown.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
